breaking the Asian record in 3:30.3, and added another bronze in the women's 4\\u00c3\\u0097100-meter medley relay alongside Wan Letian, Tang and Yang.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\", \"score\": 0.8331024269412665, \"rank\": 0.19969525972172383, \"text\": \"Wu\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\"}, {\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.9999999989863682, \"rank\": 8.312867852291784e-10, \"text\": \"Tang\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_dynasty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wang Shun claimed bronze in the men's 200-meter individual medley after touching the wall in 1:56.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Shun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Shun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chinese swimmers achieved those accomplishments while overcoming the major challenge of being the most tested team for anti-doping control at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9815822044393162, \"rank\": 0.018548583938161653, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999856755, \"rank\": 1.4387678420388649e-11, \"text\":